Description:
Deloitte Innovation Hub | All People | Feb 2025



Deloitte Women in Engineering and Allies Community

SheTalks: Conversation with Mobina!

	
Microsoft Teams Meeting
Dears,

We are excited to invite you to a 45-minute engaging session with @Salahuddin, Mobina <mailto:msalahuddin@deloitte.co.uk> , a Director in Engineering at Deloitte UK who has spent over 15 years with the firm. 

We will know more about her journey, and how she overcame challenges as a woman in technology to become a leader in technology and innovation.



Details:

*	Date: February 12th, 2025.
*	Time:

NSE DIH T&T Pharaohs Techup

Tech-Talk

 
 Topics will be covered

*	Social Network Analysis (SNA) : Kirolos Mikhail 

              is a systematic approach to analyzing relationships and interactions   

              within a network. By applying graph theory and mathematical models,   

              SNA uncovers key influencers, structural patterns, and information. 

              flow.

 

    Location: Training room & Teams meeting

    Date: Wednesday 12th February 

    Time: 1 PM to 2 PM (GMT+2)

 

 

 Food Time
       We’ll have pizza and food ready for you!! 😉

 

 

🌟 Welcome to the Tech-Talk 🌟

We’re thrilled to announce Tech-Talk, an open platform for knowledge sharing, collaboration, and exploration of tech topics across departments!  

What is Tech-Talk?  
Tech-Talk is a session where anyone can volunteer to deliver talks or spark discussions about technology. You’re invited to join the conversation. Here’s what makes Tech-Talk special:  

- Volunteer Talks: Speakers can share insights, experiences, or discoveries about tech, whether it’s their expertise or a topic they’re passionate about.  
- Ad-hoc Discussions: Bring up the latest tech news, trends, or something you think interesting/beneficial to share during the session and open the floor to dynamic, engaging discussions.  

How Does It Work?  
1. Before the session: Come prepared with topics or news items you'd like to discuss.  
2. During the session:  
   - Speakers deliver short talks on selected topics.  
   - Open discussions foster knowledge exchange, brainstorming, and collaboration.  
3. After the session: We’ll share resources in the Tech-Talk Teams channel.  

Why Join?  
- Share Knowledge: Present your work, explore challenges, or showcase a tech trend.  
- Learn Together: Gain insights from diverse perspectives across teams.  
- Connect: Build relationships with peers across departments through meaningful conversations.  

Key Details  
- Format: In-person sessions (with remote participation options).  
- Open to Everyone

Description:
My Life on a Project

Project Insights

 
Hey Team! 👋

 

🚀 Introducing My Life On A Project – A 4-Session Learning Experience! 📅✨

 

We’re thrilled to introduce My Life On A Project, a four-session series designed to provide invaluable insights into projects world. Learn directly from experienced professionals about their journey into a project, including the interview process, project scope, challenges faced, and technologies used.

 

Whether you’re leading projects, contributing to them, or still looking for your first opportunity, this is for YOU!

 

🔥 What to Expect?

Each session brings expert-led insights, interactive discussions, and practical takeaways to help you navigate projects and interviews more effectively.

 

📅 Key Details:

📍 Location: Training Room / Virtual Online via team link below

 

💡 Initiative Team:  Christine Raouf and Daniel Wassef – feel free to reach us if you have questions.

 

🕒 Time: Tuesdays from 11th February to 4th March, 1 PM - 2 PM

 

🔹Agenda

✅ How the presenter landed the project

✅ Insights into the project interview process

✅ Defining project scope and key responsibilities

✅ Technologies and tools utilized

✅ Overcoming challenges and lessons learned

 

 

📅 Session Schedule & Agenda:

🗓 Session 1: 11th February 2025 – Daniel Wassef – DevOps Cloud Consultant

🗓 Session 2: 18th February 2025 – Bishoy Hanna – DevOps Cloud Senior Manager

🗓 Session 3: 25th February 2025 – Reham Samir – DevOps Cloud Consultant

🗓 Session 4: 4th March 2025 – Sherif Mohamed – QA Testing Senior Consultant

 

💡 Why Join?

✅ Gain practical insights from experienced professionals

✅ Engage in discussions that reflect real challenges

✅ Elevate your project skills and confidence

 

🚀 Audience Priority:

If you’re an analyst, currently on the bench, or still looking for your first project, this series is designed especially for you!

 

No matter where you are in your career, this series will help you build confidence, gain valuable knowledge, and get one step closer to your next big opportunity!

 

📍 How to Join? Training room onsite / Online

 

We look forward to your participation in this insightful journey!

 

Let’s make this series a success together!

 

Best regards,

The Project Insights Team

Christine Raouf & Daniel Wassef

#MyLifeOnAProject #ProjectSuccess #LearnAndGrow 🚀

My Life on a Project

Project Insights

 
Hey Team! 👋

 

🚀 Introducing My Life On A Project – A 4-Session Learning Experience! 📅✨

 

We’re thrilled to introduce My Life On A Project, a four-session series designed to provide invaluable insights into projects world. Learn directly from experienced professionals about their journey into a project, including the interview process, project scope, challenges faced, and technologies used.

 

Whether you’re leading projects, contributing to them, or still looking for your first opportunity, this is for YOU!

 

🔥 What to Expect?

Each session brings expert-led insights, interactive discussions, and practical takeaways to help you navigate projects and interviews more effectively.

 

📅 Key Details:

📍 Location: Training Room / Virtual Online via team link below

 

💡 Initiative Team:  Christine Raouf and Daniel Wassef – feel free to reach us if you have questions.

 

🕒 Time: Tuesdays from 11th February to 4th March, 1 PM - 2 PM

 

🔹Agenda

✅ How the presenter landed the project

✅ Insights into the project interview process

✅ Defining project scope and key responsibilities

✅ Technologies and tools utilized

✅ Overcoming challenges and lessons learned

 

 

📅 Session Schedule & Agenda:

🗓 Session 1: 11th February 2025 – Daniel Wassef – DevOps Cloud Consultant

🗓 Session 2: 18th February 2025 – Bishoy Hanna – DevOps Cloud Senior Manager

🗓 Session 3: 25th February 2025 – Reham Samir – DevOps Cloud Consultant

🗓 Session 4: 4th March 2025 – Sherif Mohamed – QA Testing Senior Consultant

 

💡 Why Join?

✅ Gain practical insights from experienced professionals

✅ Engage in discussions that reflect real challenges

✅ Elevate your project skills and confidence

 

🚀 Audience Priority:

If you’re an analyst, currently on the bench, or still looking for your first project, this series is designed especially for you!

 

No matter where you are in your career, this series will help you build confidence, gain valuable knowledge, and get one step closer to your next big opportunity!

 

📍 How to Join? Training room onsite / Online

 

We look forward to your participation in this insightful journey!

 

Let’s make this series a success together!

 

Best regards,

The Project Insights Team

Christine Raouf & Daniel Wassef

#MyLifeOnAProject #ProjectSuccess #LearnAndGrow 🚀

Deloitte Innovation Hub | All People | Feb 2025



“Know your Cyber !” program.

Privacy Awareness Session.

	
Greetings,

 

Following our previous session on “Emerging Technologies Cybersecurity” as part of “Know your Cyber !” program, we are excited to invite you to our next session:

 

*	What: Privacy Awareness Session
*	When: Wednesday the 26th of February from 3 PM to 4 PM.
*	Where: Virtual over Teams.

 

Agenda:

*	Meet our Privacy Team​.
*	Data Privacy Risks and Non-Compliance.
*	Personally Identifiable Information.
*	Data Privacy Laws & Regulations with focus on GDPR.
*	Data Breach and Incident Response.
*	Q&A.

 

Join us for an enlightening session on Privacy and Digital Trust! Stay ahead of the curve as we explore the latest advancements and strategies designed to safeguard our digital future. Don’t miss out on this opportunity to broaden your knowledge and gain invaluable insights from industry experts!

Description:
From: vlogvynskyi@deloitte.co.uk
When: 2:00 PM - 2:30 PM 21 March 2025 
Subject: GenAI Data Architecture Playbooks v2 Release
Location: Microsoft Teams Meeting




 <http://www2.deloitte.com/us/en.html> 



 

United Kingdom |  AI&D | March  2025



21 March 2025

 

Hi AI & Data,

 

GenAI Data Architecture Playbook v2 Release

 

We are pleased to announce the release of our second GenAI Data Architecture playbook. Last year, we introduced our GenAI Data Architecture Playbook v1 and received fantastic feedback, providing valuable insight into our next steps and your requirements. 

 

Over the past year, we have worked to incorporate your feedback, and we are pleased to share with you what we developed with your support.

 

We would like to invite you to a brief 30-minute lunch & learn session, during which we will guide you through the developments and help you access the materials, showing you what is available and where to find all items.

 

Kinds regards

Valentyn & Ashutosh
